text: Sabine Klingbeil (born July 1947) is an East German former long track speed skater, who was active in the 1960s. When she was just 17 years old, Klingbeil represented her nation at the World Allround Speed Skating Championships for Women in 1965, finishing 25th overall.Jugend läuft um Titel, Neues Deutschland, 20 February 1965Woronina getipt as favoriete voor titel bij de schaatsmeisjes, Nieuwe Schiedamsche Courant, 5 February 1965, p.7 She also competed at other international competitions. Between 1965 and 1970 she competed at nineteen national championships (different disciplines per year), winning a total of two silver and six bronze medals. == Records== === Personal records === ==References== Category:1947 births Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Date of birth missing (living people) Category:East German sportspeople Category:Female speed skaters Category:Living people
